# A guide to editing the boot parameter


* Boot into GRUB by burning the [[iso]] and booting your machine with it

<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/hendry/2053115099/" title="grub on the CD version by Kai Hendry, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2277/2053115099_bb620f1714_m.jpg" width="240" height="180" alt="grub on the CD version" /></a>


* Edit the first menu by pressing [e]

<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/hendry/2053115105/" title="Press 'e' to edit by Kai Hendry, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2150/2053115105_9d36bd3c70_m.jpg" width="240" height="180" alt="Press 'e' to edit" /></a>

* Now edit the **BOOT PARAMETER** line by pressing [e] again!

<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/hendry/2053115107/" title="And 'e' again to do some more boot parameter hacking by Kai Hendry, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2051/2053115107_445bf53dc6_m.jpg" width="240" height="180" alt="And 'e' again to do some more boot parameter hacking" /></a>

* After editing, press [ENTER] and then [b] to boot into your own customised Webconverger!

## Some examples of what you can customise

### Your own homepage

Edit `homepage=`

See [[homepage]]

### Use Webconverger in German

append `locale=de`

see [[i18n]] for more

### Specify a HTTP proxy at 192.168.1.5:8888

append `http_proxy=http://192.168.1.5:8888`

### To do some debugging

remove `nosudo`
